Inter Beats Lecce to Narrow Gap on AC Milan; Leverkusen Wins in Germany

-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 
2011-03-20T23:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-20/inter-beats-lecce-to-narrow-gap-on-ac-milan-leverkusen-wins-in-germany.html
Inter Milan narrowed the gap on
leader AC Milan to two points in Italian soccer’s Serie A with a
1-0 home win against Lecce yesterday.  Giampaolo Pazzini scored in the 52nd minute. Two days ago,
Dorin Goian’s goal sent AC Milan to a 1-0 defeat at Palermo
while Mauro Zarate got the winner in Lazio’s 1-0 victory over
Cesena.  AC Milan has 62 points, with Inter on 60. Napoli beat
Cagliari 2-1 in yesterday’s late game to improve to 59 points,
Udinese has 56, Lazio 54 and Roma 50.  Francesco Totti  took his
Serie A scoring tally to 201 yesterday with both goals in Roma’s
2-2 draw at Fiorentina.  In  Spain , Barcelona beat Getafe 2-1 two days ago and Real  Madrid  won by the same score at city rival Atletico. Barca leads
on 78 points, five more than Real. Valencia remains on 54
points, along with Villarreal, after a 1-0 home loss to Sevilla
in yesterday’s late match.  Bayer Leverkusen narrowed the gap on Germany’s Bundesliga
leader  Borussia Dortmund  to seven points with a 2-0 home win
against Schalke yesterday. Dortmund drew 1-1 at home to Mainz
two days ago.  Lille has a five-point lead in  France  after a 2-1 win at
Brest two days ago. Marseille climbed to second, four points
behind Lille, with a 2-1 home win against Paris Saint-Germain in
yesterday’s late game.    PSV Eindhoven  still leads FC Twente by a point in the  Netherlands  after a 1-0 home win over Utrecht. Twente won 2-0 at
Excelsior. Ajax is five points further back after losing 3-2 at
Den Haag yesterday.  WEEKEND RESULTS:
===============  Italy : Lazio 1-0 Cesena; Palermo 1-0 AC Milan; Fiorentina 2-2
Roma; Bari 1-2 Chievo; Bologna 1-1 Genoa; Inter Milan 1-0 Lecce;
Juventus 2-1 Brescia; Sampdoria 0-1 Parma; Udinese 2-0 Catania;
Napoli 2-1 Cagliari.  Spain: Real Mallorca 1-0 Real Zaragoza; Barcelona 2-1 Getafe;
Atletico Madrid 1-2 Real Madrid; Hercules 0-4 Osasuna; Racing
Santander 2-1 Real Sociedad; Malaga 2-0 Espanyol; Deportivo La
Coruna 0-1 Levante; Sporting Gijon 1-0 Almeria; Athletic Bilbao
0-1 Villarreal; Valencia 0-1 Sevilla.    Germany : Borussia Dortmund 1-1 Mainz; Borussia Moenchengladbach
0-1 Kaiserslautern; Hamburg 6-2 Cologne; Eintracht Frankfurt 2-1
St. Pauli; Freiburg 1-2 Bayern Munich; Hanover 2-0 Hoffenheim;
Nuremberg 1-3 Werder Bremen; Bayer Leverkusen 2-0 Schalke;
Stuttgart 1-1 Wolfsburg.  France: Montpellier 1-4 Lens; Auxerre 2-0 Sochaux; Lorient 0-0
Saint-Etienne; Toulouse 1-1 Nice; Valenciennes 2-2 Bordeaux;
Brest 1-2 Lille; Lyon 1-1 Rennes; Monaco 0-1 Nancy; Caen 2-0
Arles-Avignon; Marseille 2-1 Paris Saint-Germain.  Netherlands: AZ Alkmaar 3-1 Vitesse Arnhem; NAC Breda 0-1
Groningen; Heracles 4-2 Heerenveen; VVV-Venlo 0-0 Willem II; NEC
Nijmegen 1-0 De Graafschap; Den Haag 3-2 Ajax; PSV 1-0 FC
Utrecht; Roda JC 3-0 Feyenoord; Excelsior 0-2 FC Twente.  To contact the reporter on this story:
